Let $O$ be the center of the octagon, and let the octagon's vertices be $A_1,A_2,...,A_8$ in clockwise order, such that $A_1A_2=A_3A_4=A_5A_6=A_7A_8=1$ and $A_2A_3=A_4A_5=A_6A_7=A_8A_1=\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}$.  Draw the radii $OA_1,OA_2,...,OA_8$.

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

pair A1, A2, A3, A4, A5, A6, A7, A8, O;

O = (0,0);
A1 = dir(22.5);
A2 = dir(67.5);
A3 = dir(112.5);
A4 = dir(157.5);
A5 = dir(202.5);
A6 = dir(247.5);
A7 = dir(292.5);
A8 = dir(337.5);

draw(A1--A2--A3--A4--A5--A6--A7--A8--cycle);
draw(O--A1);
draw(O--A2);
draw(O--A3);
draw(O--A4);
draw(O--A5);
draw(O--A6);
draw(O--A7);
draw(O--A8);

label("$A_1$", A1, NE);
label("$A_2$", A2, NE);
label("$A_3$", A3, NW);
label("$A_4$", A4, NW);
label("$A_5$", A5, SW);
label("$A_6$", A6, SW);
label("$A_7$", A7, SE);
label("$A_8$", A8, SE);
label("$O$", O, S);
[/asy]

Each central angle of the octagon measures $\frac{360^\circ}{8}=45^\circ$.  Therefore, each of the triangles $OA_1A_2,OA_2A_3,...,OA_8A_1$ is a 45-45-90 triangle.  Since the sides of length 1 and $\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}$ are adjacent, the hypotenuse of each of these triangles has length $\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}$.

The area of the octagon is equal to the sum of the areas of the eight triangles.  The area of each triangle is $\frac{1}{2}\cdot 1\cdot \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}=\frac{\sqrt{2}}{4}$, so the area of the octagon is $8\cdot \frac{\sqrt{2}}{4}=\boxed{2\sqrt{2}}$.  I hope it is correct.

ground_truth:
The octagon can be partitioned into five squares and four half squares, each with side length $\sqrt{2}/2$, so its area is \[
\displaystyle\left(5+4 \cdot \frac{1}{2}\right)\left(\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}\displaystyle\right)^{2}= \boxed{\frac{7}{2}}.
\][asy]
unitsize(2cm);
for (int i=0; i<4; ++i) {
for (int j=0; j<4; ++j) {
draw((i,0)--(i,3),dashed);
draw((0,j)--(3,j),dashed);
};}
draw((1,0)--(2,0)--(3,1)--(3,2)--(2,3)--(1,3)--(0,2)--(0,1)--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
for (int i=0; i<2; ++i) {
label("1",(0.5+2i,2.5),S);
label("1",(0.5+2i,0.5),N);}
label("$\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}$",(0,1.5),E);
label("$\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}$",(3,1.5),W);
[/asy]

